n = length(d$subID)
accuracy = data.frame(d$gain_acc,d$loss_acc,d$nongain_acc,d$nonloss_acc,d$total_acc)
rt = data.frame(d$rt_gain,d$rt_loss,d$rt_nongain,d$rt_nonloss,d$rt_mean)

Accuracy

plot1 = boxplot(accuracy, names = c("gain","loss","nongain","nonloss","total"),ylab=("percent successfully pressed before target"))

The total accuracy (55.7%) is lower than what is expected. Participants should be successfully pressing the button before the target-offset approximately 66% of the time.

Gain: mean = 60.7%; median = 62.5%; min = 16.7%; max = 94.4%

Loss: mean = 54.9%; median = 55.6%; min = 12.5%; max = 88.9%

Nongain: mean = 52.1%; median = 55.6%; min = 8.3%; max = 91.7%

Nonloss: mean = 52.5%; median = 50%; min = 0%; max = 94.4%
